In the Matter of LAKE SHORE PROPERTIES CORPORATION et al., Debtors. Marion W. FRIEND, etc., v. LAKE SHORE PROPERTIES CORPORATION. No. 5490. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. May 24, 1935. Frank E. McAllister, Morris Schaeffer, and Thomas V. Sullivan, all of Chicago, Ill., for appellants. Ralph M. Schwartzberg, Fred Bernstein, Aleck L. Bernstein, William S. Warfield, III, Richard H. Merrick, Jacob Logan Fox, John C. Tucker, George W. Swain, Aloysius B. Cawley, Joseph Z. Willner, and George I. Haight, all of Chicago, Ill., for appellees.

Before EVANS, SPARKS, and FITZHENRY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
